	</div><div class="blogs_entrybody" style="clear:both">
		(Don't pass out!  Two case file updates in two days!  Enjoy. - Chief)<br/><hr><br/>"What do you mean he hasn't entered the building yet?  The guy hasn't missed a day of work in years.  Keep calling his cell phone.  Keep me updated!" Wreed bellowed into his desk phone shortly before dropping it into the base.<br/><br/>A quick check of my watch verified that it was shortly after nine o'clock in the morning.  Things weren't going as planned in our attempt to secure Sinjin's blackberry.  Sinjin hadn't reported for work yet.<br/><br/>"Maybe he's just running late." I said, trying to lift Wreed's spirits.  "We can camp out here.  When he shows, we'll proceed as planned." <br/><br/>Wreed frowned and shook his head.<br/><br/>"This is all very unusual.  I have a bad feeling about this.  Something is up." Wreed said as he got up from his chair.  "You two are welcome to remain in my office.  I'm going to walk the floor and see if I can dig up any information."<br/><br/>"Not a problem." Scrap said as he made himself comfortable in his chair and watched Wreed exit his office.<br/><br/>I was lost in reflection while flipping through my notes and contributing to the uneasy silence that filled the room.<br/><br/>"Please tell me you have a working theory on this morning's drama." Scrap begged.<br/><br/>"I agree that something is amiss, but we don't have much to go on.  You're absolutely sure that the artifact you scraped from Sinjin's workstation said he had lunch plans today?" I asked.<br/><br/>"Positive.  I wrote it down exactly as I saw it.  They were meeting at some place called 'the cafeteria'." Scrap replied.<br/><br/>I gave Scrap a look that he was very familiar with.  It took him a mere three seconds to comprehend it.<br/><br/>"Okay, okay.  I'm on it." he said as exited Wreed's office and headed towards the receptionist's desk.<br/><br/>Scrap approached the receptionist and waited patiently for her to end her phone call.<br/><br/>"Can I help you?" she asked after slapping the 'transfer' button on her phone.<br/><br/>"I have a question.  If I were supposed to meet someone for lunch at 'the cafeteria', where would I be meeting them?" Scrap queried behind a charming smile and his usual casual demeanor.<br/><br/>The receptionist laughed.<br/><br/>"Sir, we don't have a cafeteria in this building.  Your date was probably referring to a deli about two blocks from here called O'Sharpies.  Everyone calls it 'the cafeteria' because it was a soup kitchen decades ago and is still sort of laid out like one." she stated.<br/><br/>"Peachy.  So what are you doing for lunch today?" Scrap asked as her phone rang again.<br/><br/>The receptionist immediately broke eye contact and glanced at her phone.<br/><br/>"I'm enjoying a can of soup and doing my nails.  Good morning, thank you for calling EEE.  Office of the CEO, how may I direct your call?" she said as she returned to her job duties.<br/><br/>I barely noticed Scrap returning to Wreed's office, but I recognized his patented sigh.<br/><br/>"Get turned down?" I chuckled.<br/><br/>"She had plans, wise guy.  Looks like our man Sinjin is having lunch a couple blocks down the road.  Why do I have the feeling we're eating there as well?" Scrap lamented.<br/><br/>I just smiled and returned to parsing my notes.<br/><br/>* <br/><br/>"He never showed." Wreed exclaimed as he returned to his office an hour later.  <br/><br/>"Crap." Scrap blurted.<br/><br/>"Okay, change of plans.  Scrap and I are heading over to Sinjin's lunch location.  I have stock photos of the entire management team of NC.  I need a copy of Sinjin's employee badge picture so I know what this cat looks like." I said.<br/><br/>"Done." Wreed said as he picked up the phone and contacted the security desk.<br/><br/>*<br/><br/>The walk to O'Sharpies was refreshing and tiring at the same time.  The receptionist had described it to a 't' to Scrap.  Upon entering, one is struck with the feeling of being back in grade school at lunchtime and wondering if today was salisbury steak day.<br/><br/>"Chief, let's grab that table over there by the window.  Good proximity view of the joint." Scrap suggested as he wandered toward a table barely big enough to entertain two monkeys.<br/><br/>I eyeballed my watch.  It was 10:45.<br/><br/>Shortly after sampling two hot coffees, Scrap nudged my leg under the table and pointed to a figure entering the deli.  I casually peered over my shoulder, and then looked inside the file folder placed in front of me.  <br/><br/>"That would be Sinjin." I mouthed.  <br/><br/>Sinjin peered around the deli and made eye contact with a sharply dressed man sitting five tables away.  I glanced back into my folder and started flipping pages maniacally. <br/><br/>"Something wrong, boss?" Scrap queried.<br/><br/>I closed the folder and downed the remaining coffee in my cup.<br/><br/>"That guy over there that Sinjin just sat down with... the one in the suit?" I started.<br/><br/>"Yeah, what?" Scrap whispered.<br/><br/>"I don't have a picture of that guy."<hr><br/>Read all of my case files!  Use the handy <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100710082132/http://blogs.ittoolbox.com/security/investigator/archives/official-securitymonkey-case-file-index-14787">Official SecurityMonkey Case File Index</a>!<br/><hr><br/><p><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20100710082132/http://www.numly.com/numly/verify.asp?id=72328-070308-640419-43"><img alt="numly esn" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100710082132im_/http://numly.com/numly/icon.asp?id=7232807030864041943" border="0"> 72328-070308-640419-43<br><img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20100710082132im_/http://numly.com/numly/barcode.asp?code=7232807030864041943&amp;height=20&amp;width=1&amp;mode=code39"></a><br><br>© 2007 All Rights Reserved.</p><p><hr><table width="100%" bgcolor="#FFFFCC" cellpadding="9px">
